{"tid":462992,"cid":18,"subCid":0,"title":"[哲學] 救命","createTime":"2017-11-09T05:40:47.000Z","updateTime":"2017-11-09T12:41:51.000Z","uid":157469,"like":0,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":5,"replies":[{"pid":"83bb5685a084e9ad0b902938f5c65fa1f0c6fe5b","tid":462992,"uid":157469,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-11-09T05:40:47.000Z","msg":"What is Locke's Ideational theory of meaning? Why does Locke's theory have a problem<br />\nexplaining communication? What is Locke's solution to this problem?<br />\n<br />\n有無人可以簡單解釋下 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />  在下會以身相許 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"e5838747cdc40efac42087b4b57599dcf7ff7824","tid":462992,"uid":157469,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-11-09T06:14:34.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"69cd89eb534583154d0633a1084708dff9601a9e","tid":462992,"uid":110758,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-11-09T06:55:18.000Z","msg":"自貼左先再討論"},{"pid":"4e6521cfa7b97d870d636a49809a26284fb2d13a","tid":462992,"uid":157469,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-11-09T09:01:18.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />  唔得閒自貼住"},{"pid":"32c7be43fe0f3c40370b557f7080f4fabd127bae","tid":462992,"uid":2720,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-11-09T10:04:46.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />  唔得閒自貼住</blockquote><br />\n冇圖點討論"},{"pid":"53e014833301553402a542947ae2b09027bb6219","tid":462992,"uid":35995,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-11-09T10:18:27.000Z","msg":"自己睇啦<br />\nBasic:<br />\nAlex Miller, philosophy of language, pp.36-41.<br />\nAdvance:<br />\nE. J. Lowe, Locke's essay..., ch.7."},{"pid":"2c9f9616a9e9b65c96ffe2314d23ec9c8977e3aa","tid":462992,"uid":126973,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-11-09T12:41:51.000Z","msg":"<blockquote>What is Locke's Ideational theory of meaning? Why does Locke's theory have a problem<br />\nexplaining communication? What is Locke's solution to this problem?<br />\n<br />\n有無人可以簡單解釋下 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />  在下會以身相許 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n<br />\n<br />\nideational theories 就係話意義對應 speaker嘅有內容嘅 mental states<br />\n好直觀嘅，你講「蘋果」，呢個詞嘅意義，就係你腦海果個蘋果嘅 image<br />\n<br />\n根本就好 naive嘅語言觀來 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n大家嘅 mental states 都唔同架麻  <br />\n所以，大家用「蘋果」原來係有唔同意義 <br />\nA 講 「蘋果」係對應佢自己嘅 mental image<br />\nB 講「蘋果」係對應佢自己嘅 mental image<br />\n<br />\n咁咪大家雖然講同一個詞，但根據 ideational theories，<br />\n大家其實係講緊唔同嘅野，咁咪牛頭唔搭馬嘴，溝通唔到<br />\n<br />\nLocke類似話雖然係咁，但 words係 secretly refer to the ideas of other people<br />\n所以可以明白人地講嘅野"}]}